PyCi Coding Standards(draft)

* General conventions
  Please use TEMPLATE.py as the template for all your Python
  source. Especially, all non-ascii characters should be in UTF-8
  coding.

  Only add #!(sharp-bang) for scripts.

* For program coding
  Please follow PEP-8 [1]

* For document
  Please use Epydoc's Epytext Markup Language [2] in your docstrings.

[1] http://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008/
[2] http://epydoc.sourceforge.net/manual-epytext.html
